@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "BackEnd";
    var isParticipant = User.IsInRole("BackEnd");
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Back End Development</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <style>
        .enroll-btn {
            display: block;
            width: 200px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: green;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        .message {
            display: none;
            margin-top: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            color: red;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .contact-btn {
            display: none;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: blue;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

            .contact-btn:hover {
                background-color: darkblue;
            }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Back End Development</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>1. Introduction to Back End Development</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>What is Back End Development?</li>
                <li>Role of Servers and Databases</li>
                <li>APIs and Data Processing</li>
                <li>Overview of Back End Technologies</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>2. Server-Side Programming</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Introduction to Server-Side Languages</li>
                <li>Node.js Basics</li>
                <li>Express.js for Server Setup</li>
                <li>Handling HTTP Requests and Responses</li>
                <li>Session Management</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>3. Working with Databases</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Introduction to Databases</li>
                <li>SQL vs NoSQL</li>
                <li>Connecting to Databases (MySQL, MongoDB)</li>
                <li>Database Operations (CRUD)</li>
                <li>Database Security and Optimization</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>4. Building RESTful APIs</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>What is an API?</li>
                <li>REST Architecture</li>
                <li>Building a Simple REST API with Node.js</li>
                <li>Authentication and Authorization in APIs</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>5. Testing and Debugging Back End Applications</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Unit Testing and Integration Testing</li>
                <li>Debugging Techniques for Back End</li>
                <li>Logging and Error Handling</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <button class="enroll-btn" onclick="handleEnroll()">Enroll Now</button>

        <div class="message" id="message">
            You must send a cost of course to Vodafone Cash at number 01095647382, and after that, call a secretary to add you to the list of students in this course.
        </div>

        <a class="contact-btn" id="contact-btn" asp-area="" asp-controller="Message" asp-action="Index" asp-route-RecieverType="Secertary" asp-route-coursename="backend">Call Us</a>

    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>© 2024 Your Course Platform</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        function handleEnroll() {
            var isParticipant = @Html.Raw(Json.Serialize(isParticipant));

            if (isParticipant) {
                window.location.href = '@Url.Action("CoursePage", "Course")';
            } else {
                var messageDiv = document.getElementById('message');
                var contactBtn = document.getElementById('contact-btn');
                messageDiv.style.display = 'block';
                contactBtn.style.display = 'inline-block';
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
